#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:58
msgid "Here instance variables ``l1`` and ``l2`` are assigned to the two BuildLine objects and the ``ThreePointArc`` references the beginning of the straight line with ``l1 @ 0`` and the end with ``l1 @ 1``.  The ``@`` operator takes a float (or integer) parameter between 0 and 1 and determines a position at this fractional position along the line's length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:64
msgid "This example can be improved on further by calculating the mid-point of the arc as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:72
msgid "Here ``l1 @ 0.5`` finds the center of ``l1`` while ``l1 @ 0.5 + (0, 1)`` does a vector addition to generate the point ``(1,1)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:75
msgid "To make the design even more parametric, the height of the arc can be calculated from ``l1`` as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:83
msgid "The arc height is now calculated as ``(0, l1.length / 2)`` by using the ``length`` property of ``Edge`` and ``Wire`` shapes.  At this point the ``ThreePointArc`` is fully parametric and able to generate the same shape for any horizontal line."
msgstr ""

