#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:119
msgid "BuildLine to BuildSketch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:121
msgid "As mentioned previously, one of the two primary reasons to create BuildLine objects is to use them in BuildSketch.  When a BuildLine context manager exits and is within the scope of a BuildSketch context manager it will transfer the generated line to BuildSketch. The BuildSketch :meth:`~operations_sketch.make_face` or :meth:`~operations_sketch.make_hull`  operations are then used to transform the line (specifically a list of Edges) into a Face - the native BuildSketch objects."
msgstr ""

