#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:157
msgid "BuildLine to BuildPart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:159
msgid "The other primary reasons to use BuildLine is to create paths for BuildPart :meth:`~operations_generic.sweep` operations. Here some curved and straight segments define a path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:173
msgid "There are few things to note from this example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:175
msgid "The @ and % operators are used to create a plane normal to the beginning of the path with which to create the circular section used by the sweep operation (this plane is not one of the ordinal planes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/build_line.rst:178
msgid "Both the path generated by BuildLine and the section generated by BuildSketch have been transferred to BuildPart when each of them exit."
